Weekupdate - halftime:
Under the week we worked a lot at the institute. We could complete quite a few tasks...
We have been cooking a lot - noodles with pesto and Burritos for example. Under the week at the evening we did not do that much, since we were pretty exhausted from working and no students are here because they are on vacation. 
But to make it up we used the weekend to visit some places in the area.
On Saturday Roanoake, where we visited downtown and the Virginia Museum of Transportation, which was really awesome and worth a visit. On Saturday we drove to Christiansburg where Julian saw for the first time in his live a Walmart, which is basically a insanely big shopping center, where you can find just anything...
After that we ate in the Texas Roadhouse - the food was great!
At about 6 pm we started hiking back to Blacksburg on the famous Huckleberry Trail. A really beautiful trail with stunning Nature sights. Decades ago there were coalmines in this area. Even today we could find coal on the forest floor...
Thanks for reading and we wish a great next week 😉.

