☀️ Batumi Vibes: Solar Energy & Sunshine Adventures!

From April 5–14, Irish Really Cool Adventure team joined an amazing Erasmus project in Batumi, Georgia – gettin more aware of solar energy while having the time of our lives!

We did non formal education activities, learn and shared our ideas with young people from across Europe.

But wait… it wasn’t just workshops!
We explored Batumi's wild side too:

Took in the views from the Alphabet Tower
Walked along Batumi Boulevard (felt like Dubai!)
Watched the Ali & Nino statue come alive
Hiked in the stunning Mtirala National Park
Visited botanic gardens
Tried the famous cheesy khachapuri (so good!)

This was a perfect mix of learning and fun.
New friends, new knowledge, and loads of memories!

Batumi, you were a dream.
We’ll be back!

